citeinfo.title: Major River Lines Florida

descript.abstract: This GIS data set represents Florida's 50 major rivers as identified in the "Florida Rivers Assessment", completed for the Florida Department of Natural Resources (DNR) in December 1989 by Florida Resources and Environmental Analysis Center (FREAC) at Florida State University. Florida Marine Research Institute (FMRI) staff downloaded these data from the Florida Department of Environmental Protection (FDEP) FTP site. These data are available in both polygon and line format.
descript.purpose: These data represent major rivers for cartographic reference only. The original source scale and accuracy is not known, therefore these data are not appropriate for analysis. Use with caution.
descript.supplinf:
Prior to July 1, 2004, the Fish and Wildlife Research Institute (FWRI) was known as the Florida Marine Research Institute (FMRI). The institute name has not been changed in historical data sets or references to work completed by the Florida Marine Research Institute. The institute name has been changed in references to ongoing research, new research, and contact information.
The line data set includes additional smaller streams not included in the polygon data set. Some rivers have changed course since the 1989 source date. FMRI has not made any edits to the positional accuracy of these data. Use with caution.

procstep.procdesc:
FDEP performed the following:
In September, 2000, the shapefile of this dataset was inserted into Spatial Database Engine (SDE 3.0.2). SDE is ESRI's client/server technology for storing and managing spatial data in a relational database management system (RDBMS) and for spatially enabling existing RDBMS tables. For this dataset, ARC/INFO specific fields, such as <cover># and <cover>-id were dropped.
FMRI staff downloaded the shapefiles of this data set from the FDEP FTP site. FMRI reprojected these data into Albers NAD 83 and loaded the shapefile into ArcSDE 8.3
